# CREÅTIVE STEEPING: Mobile Spatial Analysis & Responsive Design Training Brief

**Prepared For:** Development Partner Team  
**Prepared By:** Manus AI  
**Site Under Review:** [creativesteeping.com](https://creativesteeping.com)  
**Audit Basis:** Six mobile screenshots (iPhone, ~390px viewport) + live site code inspection  
**Context:** CREÅTIVE STEEPING is a creative self-care retreat — a sonic soulsite where the Sonnet Engine, the Steeperverse, and the Steeping Space architecture must cohere as a single, immersive, meditative experience.

---

## Executive Summary

The first mobile view of CREÅTIVE STEEPING reveals a site whose desktop spatial logic has not yet been translated into a mobile-native language. The experience is architecturally rich — the Sonnet Engine, the Lore Capture sections, the Vessel Matrix, the Crossroads, and the Flavor Mode system are all conceptually powerful. But on a 390px viewport, the current implementation collapses that architecture into a series of overlapping, competing, and inaccessible elements that fracture the meditative pacing the site is designed to produce.

This brief provides a full-bodied spatial analysis of every observed issue, paired with precise responsive design directives. It is organized as a training document for the development team: each section names the problem, explains the spatial logic behind it, and prescribes the exact technical resolution. The goal is not simply to "make it fit" — it is to ensure that the mobile experience is a deliberately curated, vertical journey into the essence of the user's flavor.

